-- ECB says covered bond purchase total 24.756 bln euros
-- By Paul Carrel
-- Mon Dec 15, 2014 09:53AM EST
-- None



FRANKFURT, Dec 15 (Reuters) - The European Central Bank bought 3.829 billion euros ($4.76 billion) of covered bonds last week, taking the total amount it has spent on such debt under its new purchase programme to 24.756 billion euros.

The ECB said on Monday it had also bought 788 million euros worth of asset-backed securities as of Dec. 12, an increase of 187 million from the prior week.